I later found that me and Gotye could not make sense. He said that we would still be friends. I honestly admit I'm glad it was over. But, I still think back to when Anxiety cut him off when it didn't have to. Now we'll have to make out like it never happened and now we're nothing. We didn't even need love, though. Everyone treated us like strangers and that felt so rough. Doechii really didn't have to stoop so low. Now, my friends will have to collect my records and I'll have to change my number. I just realized how deep the symbolism in this video goes. At the start, Gotye is unpainted â€” fully visible â€” meaning she still recognized him, still held on to some emotional connection. But as the video progresses, he slowly fades into the background, literally becoming â€œsome bodyâ€ she used to know. The wordplay is genius: "somebody" as in a person from the past, and "some body" as in a vague, faceless figure now lost in memory. His emotional breakdown shows heâ€™s just now realizing what he lost â€” but itâ€™s too late. When Kimbra enters, sheâ€™s already painted, already faded, like she was disappearing emotionally long before he noticed. Her verse reframes everything: she wasnâ€™t cold â€” she was hurt, dismissed, and now done. And when she walks away and her paint fades completely, it shows sheâ€™s free, while he remains stuck in guilt and realization â€” still painted, still invisible. This video isnâ€™t just about heartbreak â€” itâ€™s about how we only truly see someone after theyâ€™re gone.

Yes and no, I used it to reformulate it in a better way because this was difficult to explain. I came up myself with the wordplay, meaning about the paint, emotional roller-coaster and how he himself is truly the one who saw her another way before he did. I say this rarely, in fact never. But this song is in fact perfect. Being almost entirely composed from other songs it is a sampled collage of fleeting and incomplete memories that are warped and layered over one another, creating a tightly woven tapestry of the past. It is all the best bits of memories roughly yet passionately stitched together to create a masterpiece that is not just a break up song, but THE break up song. Every millisecond of this song evokes every memory of everyone I have loved and lost in my journey to understand who I am and what I am to share with the world. Many songs have lyrical mastery, harmonic adeptness or just pure soul, but this song has everything all firmly baked into it's very being. This is timeless art and was instantly recognized by everyone as such, even if they didn't outwardly realize it immediately. Pure genius.
